# Network Ports and Services

This folder contains my notes from the second networking lesson.

During this lesson, I learned how computers use network ports to run multiple services on the same IP address, how TCP and UDP differ, and how to inspect active network connections on Windows.

## Topics covered

- Why network ports are necessary
- Common network ports
- Open ports and cybersecurity
- Inspecting connections with `netstat`
- TCP vs UDP
- IP address, port and protocol
- Why TCP is more reliable than UDP

